-- Mol CEO May Go to Zagreb in Probe If Hungary Agrees, Globus Says
-- B y   M i c h a e l   W i n f r e y
-- 2013-08-16T17:52:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-16/mol-ceo-may-go-to-zagreb-in-probe-if-hungary-agrees-globus-says.html
Mol CEO Zsolt Hernadi will go to
 Croatia , where prosecutors have asked Hungary to assist with his
interrogation, if authorities from both countries agree,
newspaper Globus quotes Hernadi as saying in interview published
on its website today.
* NOTE: Croatian prosecutors in 2011 asked Hungarian judicial
authorities to arrange the interrogation of Hernadi over his
role in the sale of Croatian refiner INA to Mol in 2009. Request
was rejected.
* NOTE: Croatian officials have renewed an investigation of
Hernadi over his alleged role in corruption trial of former
Croatian Prime Minister Ivo Sanader; link to story: NSN
